---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About — Mingz" showBackLink={true}>
  <header class="py-12 border-b border-border-custom">
    <p class="text-[11px] tracking-wider uppercase text-ink-muted mb-3">About me</p>
    <h1>
      "Ming" means <span class="text-vermillion">bright</span>,
    </h1>
    <br>
    <p>and that's exactly what I bring to the table.</p>
  </header>

  <section class="py-12 max-w-[640px]">
    <h3>I'm a designer who is both left and right brained.</h3><br>

    <p class="text-base text-ink-muted mb-6 leading-[1.8]">
      I was a science student all my life till I did a switch to Fine Arts in college. I enjoy creating solutions that are <b>grounded</b> in <b>research and data</b>, while I inject some of my <b>creative flair</b> into the process and design.
    </p>

     <h3>I'm energetic and hands-on team leader and player.</h3><br>
    <p class="text-base text-ink-muted mb-6 leading-[1.8]">
      I worked in the banking and government-tech spaces during my 5 year long career as a UX Designer/Researcher, though most of the time I saw myself as a problem solver. My scope of work involved more than just designing digital products. I redesigned company processes and workflows, led countless design workshops, created design systems, introduced design governance, co-led a design team, and mentored juniors and interns who all became confident designers themselves today! 
    </p>

    <h3>I took a 3 year long sidequest to learn more about HCI and UX, and figure out the meaning of being a designer in today's world. </h3><br>
    <p class="text-base text-ink-muted mb-6 leading-[1.8]">
      Deciding to take a 3 year long sabbatical from the corporate world to pursue my Masters in Human Computer Interaction (HCI) in the United States was not an easy decision. However, I wanted to take time off to pick up more theoretical knowledge that would back my research practices up. I also wanted to use the time to discover more research interests in the HCI space that includes designing for older adults, designing low-tech solutions and participatory design.
    </p>
   <p class="text-base text-ink-muted mb-6 leading-[1.8]">
      I like exploring the tensions and synergy within human-computer interactions. Especially in today’s AI-driven age, I am especially interested in identifying ethical and thoughtful AI use cases that will be an aid, and not an ailment to humans in both the short and long run.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base text-ink-muted mb-6 leading-[1.8]">
      During this sidequest I also picked up 3d printing, vibe coding, tarot card reading, crocheting, and lots of rave-related crafting. Who says sabbaticals can't be fun!!
    </p>

    <h3>I also have a life outside of work.</h3><br>
  <p class="text-base text-ink-muted mb-6 leading-[1.8]">
      I enjoy crafting, journalling, recipe testing, backpacking, EDM music (mainly techno, dubstep, afrohouse and bass), digital and film photography, and being the vocalist of my band, The Paperbaggers. My hobbies provide me with many opportunities to connect with people from all walks of life, and I love engaging in conversations with them to see different facets and realities of life through their eyes and words.
    
    <h2 class="mt-10 mb-4">What I bring</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-ink-muted mb-6 leading-[1.8]">
      MORE PASSION, MORE ENERGY, MORE FOOTWORK  <br>
      <br>
      and also, End-to-end product design, UX research (qualitative and quantitative), service design, design ops, and workshop facilitation. I'm comfortable moving between strategy and execution, and between ambiguous early-stage problems and mature systems that need refinement.
    </p>

  
  </section>
</Layout>
